# CitizenReady - Coding Rules

## Tech Stack
- Next.js 14+ with App Router
- TypeScript
- Tailwind CSS + shadcn/ui
- Supabase (Auth + Database)
- Zod for validation
- Server Actions for mutations

## Code Style
- Use functional components with TypeScript
- Prefer Server Components by default
- Add 'use client' only when needed (hooks, interactivity)
- Use Server Actions for all mutations
- Return { success?, data?, error? } from all actions
- Never throw errors in Server Actions

## File Organization
- Place Server Actions in /actions
- Keep types in /types
- Use /lib for utilities and Supabase clients
- Components in /components with subfolders by domain

## Database
- All queries use RLS - no service role key in frontend
- Use createClient() from lib/supabase/server in Server Components
- Use createClient() from lib/supabase/client in Client Components
- Validate all inputs with Zod schemas from lib/validations.ts

## UI/UX
- Use shadcn/ui components
- Mobile-first responsive design
- Loading states for all async operations
- Error boundaries for error handling
- Accessible forms with proper labels and ARIA attributes
